      • getValues

        public final String[] getValues(String name)
        Returns an array of values of the field specified as the method parameter. This method returns an empty array when there are no matching fields. It never returns null. For IntField, LongField, FloatField and DoubleField it returns the string value of the number. If you want the actual numeric field instances back, use getFields().
        Parameters:
        name - the name of the field
        Returns:
        a String[] of field values
